<span id="freeTextContainer8400295666634394839">.<br/><br/>A Hidden Fire in the introductory volume of The Elemental Mysteries by Elizabeth Hunter. <br/><br/><b> <i> A young student librarian is thrown into the immortal world when she takes a job from a mysterious Italian scholar, Giovanni Vecchio. Beatrice is drawn to the mystery--and her new employer--but can she survive a vampire world ruled by power, politics, and blood-lust? <br/><br/>How far will Giovanni go to find a library missing for five hundred years? <i> </i></i></b><br/><br/>Beatrice De Novo, a university student working in the library, i</span>
  <span id="freeText8400295666634394839" style="display:none">.<br /><br />A Hidden Fire in the introductory volume of The Elemental Mysteries by Elizabeth Hunter. <br /><br /><b> <i> A young student librarian is thrown into the immortal world when she takes a job from a mysterious Italian scholar, Giovanni Vecchio. Beatrice is drawn to the mystery--and her new employer--but can she survive a vampire world ruled by power, politics, and blood-lust? <br /><br />How far will Giovanni go to find a library missing for five hundred years? <i> </i></i></b><br /><br />Beatrice De Novo, a university student working in the library, intrigues a mysterious Italian scholar, Giovanni Vecchio. Their paths cross and intertwine in the most fascinating ways. They are drawn to each other inexplicably in spite of the danger surrounding this mysterious man.<br /><br />I'm not usually a fan of vampires, but this was an amazing paranormal story filled with humor, intrigue, and passion. <br /><br />I just LOVE books and the captivating aspect of the compulsion in the story may have tugged on my heart quite a bit.<br /><br />The chemistry and the compulsion of the storyline grabbed me, compelling me with captivation throughout the entire adventure. <br /><br />There is profanity, but it was not blatantly offensive. I still prefer that it is omitted from my literary adventures. There were no sexual encounters that I recall.<br /><br />I couldn't wait to get the rest of the series.<br /><br />---------------------------------------------<br /><br />A Hidden Fire: Elemental Mysteries, Book 1 <br />Elizabeth Hunter, Author<br />Print Length: 398 pages<br /></span>
